FBIS4-43179 "drweu114_j_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-114 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY PDS Leader Ochetto Resigns After European Elections PDS Leader Ochetto Resigns After European Elections AU1306141094 Paris AFP in English 1355 GMT 13 Jun 94 AU1306141094 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Rome, June 13 (AFP) -- Reformed communist (PDS) [Democratic Party of the Left] party chief Achille Occhetto resigned, the PDS press department announced Monday [13 June]. The PDS garnered 19.1 percent of the votes in Sunday's European Parliament elections against 20.4 percent in the March general elections in Italy.
